data.title: Troubled school has top results

data.text:
AN INDEPENDENT school hit by internal divisions and the departure of its head teacher has achieved the country’s best A-level results.

Winchester College takes first place in The Times table of results from independent schools published today, with its 146 students achieving an average of almost four A grades each.

The school saw 409 of its 559 entries awarded the top grade, putting it narrowly ahead of Westminster School.

Winchester, whose motto is “Manners Makyth Man”, has had a stormy year. Nick Tate resigned after two and a half years as headmaster in February, citing “family reasons”.
